In Unreal Engine 5, coordinates were shifted from 32-bit float (`FVector`) to 64-bit double-precision vectors (`FVector3d` or alias `FVector`) to allow building maps that are millions of units wide without precision jitter:

```cpp
// UE4 representation (32-bit float)
struct FVector_UE4 {
    float X, Y, Z;
};

// UE5 representation (64-bit double precision)
struct FVector_UE5 {
    double X, Y, Z;
};
```
